Nigeria received $223.3 million worth of foreign direct investment (FDI) between January and May 2022, an increase of 3.7 per cent when compared to $215.3 million recorded in the corresponding period of 2021. However when compared to the period of 2020, FDI declined by 7.5 per cent from $241.5 million received in the period under review. This is according to figures from the Central Bank of Nigeria (CBN). Nigeriaâ€™s foreign direct investment has dwindled significantly recently, hitting a record low of $698.8 million in 2021. 